summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of Two Hundred Fifty ($250.00) Dollars from the general fund of the City of Seattle to pay the suit and claim of Mrs. Sadie Rose for personal injuries received by her on the 27th day of July, 1913, while walking on the sidewalk at the corner of Orcas Street and Maynard Avenue, in said City, at about the hour of 10 o'clock P.M., and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
